cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with object detection and semantic labeling in 3D point clouds obtained from RGB-D cameras, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The method proposed in the paper is designed for robotic perception, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also uses a graphical model and machine learning techniques, which are common in the fields of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with geometric relationships and spatial reasoning, which are relevant to the field of computer graphics (cs.GR).
